Arnold Schwarzenegger is an Austrian-American bodybuilder, actor, businessman, and politician. He had a successful career as a bodybuilder in the 1970s and 1980s, winning Mr. Universe and Mr. Olympia several times. As an actor, his breakthrough role was Conan the Barbarian in 1982, and he is best known for playing the Terminator character in five Terminator films. Schwarzenegger served as the 38th Governor of California from 2003 to 2011.
